== Japanese ==
===Stroke Order===
[[Image:Japanese Hiragana A.png]]

===Etymology===
Simplified form of the kanji [[安]]

===Hiragana character===
'''あ''' (''a'')

# the [a] phoneme, typically in words of Japanese origin
#: The first character of the [[hiragana]] [[syllabary]], it is analogous to [[ア]] (''a'') in the [[katakana]] syllabary. The next hiragana character is [[い]] (''i'').

===Related terms===
* For a list of words starting with あ (''a'') see: [[Index:Japanese/あ]]

===Kanji Reading===
[[Category:Kanji reading]]
'''あ''' (''a'')

* {{japdef|亜|[[secondary]]}}
*[[阿]]
*[[唖]]
*[[痾]]
*[[鴉]]

